definition.value: A stilbenoid that is ethane in which one of the hydrogens is replaced by a 4-hydroxyphenyl group and one of the hydrogens of the remaining methyl group is replaced by a 4-hydroxy-3,5-dimethoxyphenyl group.
An (R)-3-hydroxyacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (R)-3-hydroxyoctanoic acid.

A glycononaosylceramide in which the sugar component is a linear heptasaccharide made up from galactose, N-acetylgalactosamine, glucose and N-acetylglucosamine residues, branched with L-fucosyl residues at two of the galactose residues in the chain.
A L-glutamyl ester that is the  alpha-methyl ester derivative of L-glutamic acid.
An acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 2,6-dihydroxycyclohexane-1-carboxylic acid.
A hydroxyacyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of 2-hydroxyglutaric acid.
A member of the class of caprolactams that is azepane substituted by an oxo group at position 2.
A (2R)-2-hydroxy monocarboxylic acid consisting of lactic acid having a sulfanyl group at the 3-position.
A UDP-N-acetyl-mannosaminouronic acid in which the N-acetyl-mannosaminouronic acid fragment has D-configuration.

A member of the class of azobenzenes that is azobenzene in which the para position of one of the phenyl groups is substituted by a carboxy group, whilst that of the other phenyl group is substituted by a sulfo group.
A pentasaccharide that is stachiose which has an additional unit of alpha-D-galactopyranose attached by a 1->6 glycosidic linkage to the terminal galactosyl residue.
The D-stereoisomer of threose.
A  monomethoxybenzene that consists of phenol with a methoxy substituent at the ortho position.
A (9Z)-12-hydroxyoctadec-9-enoic acid in which the 12-hydroxy group has R-configuration..
A cinchona alkaloid consisting of cinchonine with the hydrogen at the 6-position of the quinoline ring substituted by methoxy.
Phenylacetylglycine hydroxylated at the phenyl C-4 position.
A tetrahydroxyflavone that consists of isoorientin substituted by a rhamnosyl moiety at position 2".
A farnesane sesquiterpenoid that is dodeca-2,6,10-triene substituted by methyl groups at positions 3, 7 and 11 and a hydroxy group at position 1.
A D-fructofuranose 2,6-bisphosphate with a beta-configuration at the anomeric centre.
A 3beta-sterol consisting of stigmastan-3beta-ol with double bonds at positions 5 and 24(28). The double bond at postion 24(28) adopts a Z-configuration.
A member of the class of benzamides that results from the formal condensation of  benzoic acid with the amino group of 4-methoxyanthranilic acid.
An oleoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl group at position 1 is (9Z)-octadecenoyl (oleoyl) and the hydroxy group at position 2 is unsubstituted.
A one-carbon compound that is ammonia in which one of the hydrogens is replaced by a carboxy group. Although carbamic acid derivatives are common, carbamic acid itself has never been synthesised.
A tolualdehyde compound with the methyl substituent at the 4-position.
A dichlorobenzene carrying chloro groups at positions 1 and 4.
A member of the class of acrylamides that results from the formal condensation of acrylic acid with ammonia.
A member of the class of 7-hydroxyisoflavones that is 7-hydroxyisoflavone substituted by additional hydroxy groups at positions 5, 2' and 4' and a prenyl group at position 3'.
A tertiary amino compound that is ammonia in which each of the hydrogens is substituted by a 2-hydroxyethyl group.
A tetrahydrofolyl glutamate consisting of a tetrahydrofolyl group linked via an amide bond to a poly(gamma-glutamyl chain)
